# Commit title format:
# <emoji> <type>(<scope>): <imperative summary>
#
# Examples:
# :sparkles: feat(parser): add support for wildcard imports
# :bug: fix(cli): handle empty input arguments
# :books: docs(readme): document local development setup
#
# Description of changes:
# - Summarize the concrete changes made.
# - Explain the motivation when it is not obvious.
# - Reference issues/PRs as #<issue-number> and GH-<PR-number> when relevant.
#
# Keep each commit focused on one category when possible.
#
# Common types:
# feat     - new feature
# fix      - bug fix
# refactor - code restructuring without behavior change
# docs     - documentation only
# test     - tests added or updated
# chore    - maintenance / tooling / housekeeping
# ci       - CI configuration and automation
# perf     - performance improvements
# style    - formatting / style-only changes
# build    - build system or dependency changes
# revert   - revert a previous commit
#
# Common emojis:
# :art:                    style / formatting / cosmetic
# :sparkles:               new feature
# :bug:                    bug fix
# :recycle:                refactor
# :books:                  documentation
# :rotating_light:         tests
# :racehorse:              performance
# :scissors:               removal
# :floppy_disk:            data
# :bar_chart:              plots / metrics
# :bookmark:               version tag / release
# :wrench:                 tooling / config / chore
# :construction_worker:    ci / automation
#
# Template:
# <emoji> <type>(<scope>): <imperative summary>
#
# Description of changes:
# - 
# - 
#
# Motivation:
# - 
#
# References:
# - 
